<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100383977032525></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100383977032525><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4383&mid=100383977032525>Guild assistance</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4383&mid=100383977032525#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=80919><span id= >TruKing</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 23rd 8:22 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well i have to say that you really dont need guild assistance to get this item.  I dual box(play 2 computers at once) and i camp a spot where i kill on average 8 mob's per spawn cycle.  If i can do it with just a cleric and monk then it is easily done with an average group of low 50 maybe even lower. <br><br>As far as the question of who this should go to.  Well its the best tradeable monk legs out there.  Not counting the flayed barb of course since those are out of reach of basically everybody at this time.  They are also decent rogue legs and int caster legs.  Melee can easily get better then these with gladiator chain or kromriff military legs.  They dont have as many hp as any of the quest legs so when these dropped for me the first time i gave to a necro because she wanted a nice ac piece and yes ALL classes need ac.<br><br>Monks quite often tank and do need high ac and hp.  It's very easy for a monk to gain agro and we need to be able to survive that while we feign or stop attacking otherwise you lose out on a lot of damage.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
